time: Time of the process event. All data starts with a time epoch of 1 using a time resolution of 1 second.
user: The user who caused the event in the format user@domain
event: Event type: either start or end
lastCompromiseTvent: The time of the last compromise event on the computer. Time of 0 indicates no known compromise at the time of the event.
redTeamUser: Flag indicating whether the user is known to be related to a compromise event on this machine. 0 indicates the user on this computer is not known to be red team; 1 indicates the user is known to be red team.
